<stack-static>
    <statement><p><p>A delivery drone is programmed to deliver two packages along a straight East-West flight path. The drone's motion is recorded as follows:</p>
<ul>
    <li>It flies <m>{150}</m> meters East to deliver the first package.</li>
    <li>It then turns around and flies <m>{74}</m> meters West to deliver the second package.</li>
</ul>

<p>
</p><ol>
    <li>What is the total distance travelled by the drone? <fillin characters="10" name="ans1"/> m </li>
    <li>What is the drone's displacement from its starting point? <fillin characters="10" name="ans2"/> m </li>
</ol>
</p></statement>
    <solution><p><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<alert>1. Total Distance</alert>
<p>Distance is the total length of the path travelled, regardless of direction:</p>
<p>
<md>
<mrow>\text{Distance} \amp = \text{Leg 1} + \text{Leg 2}</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = {150} \text{ m} + {74} \text{ m}</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = {224} \text{ m}</mrow>
</md>
</p>

<alert>2. Displacement</alert>
<p>Displacement is the change in position (Final Position - Initial Position). Since the drone moved in opposite directions, we treat East as positive and West as negative:</p>
<p>
<md>
<mrow>\text{Displacement} \amp = \text{Final Position} - \text{Initial Position}</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = {150} \text{ m} - {74} \text{ m}</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = {76} \text{ m East}</mrow>
</md>
</p></p></solution>
    <answer><p><m>224</m></p></answer>
    <answer><p><m>76</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>